<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="230" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dix</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-14"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 14, 1866.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I herewith transmit to you for your
                            information a copy of a communication of the 11th instant, from the
                            Secretary of War, accompanied by two telegraphic reports from General
                            Sheridan relative to the present condition of affairs on the Rio
                            Grande.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John A. Dix</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>